717574f.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 53rd Street
717574f.text:
Broadway, south from West 53rd Street, showing in the foreground
the B. S. Moss, Broadway Theatre at the S.W. corner of the aforementioned
point. Note the varied electrical signs on this, the "White Way" as
viewed towards Times Square.
About 1932.
E. C. I. Publishers.

717575f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 53rd Street (West)
717575f-a.text:
Broadway, west side, north from West 53rd Street, showing prominently
two 12-story structures, 828-830 and 832-838. The first of these,houses
the Manhattan Music Hall and the latter the Hotel Cumberland (formerly
the Adlon). The hotel is directly at the S.W. corner of West 54th Street.
This set consists of a negative and a positive view.
September 1935.
W.P.A. Photo.

713664f-a.title: Manhattan: 53rd Street (West) - Broadway
713664f-a.text:
Wost 53rd Street, west from Broadway, showing the prog-
ress made on the W. P. A. repaving project at this point.
April 23, 1937
W. P. A., photo
Five Boroughs Project
